- [1] user: I'm dealing with frequent socket drops in our production React app when users switch networks or lose signal. Currently, our reconnect logic just retries every 3 seconds, which is DDOSing our gateway during minor AWS outages. I need a robust reconnect function using exponential backoff with jitter. We already have a heartbeat ping/pong to detect silent drops, but once the socket actually closes, we need a smarter recovery. Can you show me a clean TypeScript implementation?

- [1] assistant: Here is a robust reconnection strategy using exponential backoff with "Full Jitter" to prevent thundering herd problems when your socket gateway recovers.

```typescript
class WebSocketManager {
  private ws: WebSocket | null = null;
  private attempts = 0;
  private readonly baseDelay = 1000; // 1 second
  private readonly maxDelay = 30000; // 30 seconds
  private heartbeatTimer?: number;

  constructor(private url: string) {}

  public connect() {
    this.ws = new WebSocket(this.url);

    this.ws.onopen = () => {
      this.attempts = 0; // Reset backoff on successful connection
      this.startHeartbeat();
    };

    this.ws.onclose = () => {
      this.cleanup();
      this.queueReconnect();
    };
  }

  private queueReconnect() {
    // Exponential backoff: base * 2^attempts
    const exponentialDelay = this.baseDelay * Math.pow(2, this.attempts);
    const cappedDelay = Math.min(exponentialDelay, this.maxDelay);

    // Add Full Jitter: random value between 0 and cappedDelay
    const jitteredDelay = Math.random() * cappedDelay;

    console.warn(`Socket closed. Reconnecting in ${Math.round(jitteredDelay)}ms (Attempt ${this.attempts + 1})`);

    setTimeout(() => {
      this.attempts++;
      this.connect();
    }, jitteredDelay);
  }

  private startHeartbeat() {
    this.heartbeatTimer = window.setInterval(() => {
      if (this.ws?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {
        this.ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'ping' }));
      }
    }, 15000);
  }

  private cleanup() {
    clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);
    if (this.ws) {
      this.ws.onclose = null; // Prevent duplicate trigger during manual close
      this.ws.close();
    }
  }
}
```

This spreads the reconnect spikes across a wide window. Under high load, `Math.random() * cappedDelay` ensures that 10,000 disconnected clients won't hit your servers in identical 2-second waves.

